Name: skin angiosarcoma
Definition: An angiosarcoma and hemangioma of skin and malignant skin vascular tumor and sarcoma of skin that is located_in the skin and results_in an enlarged bruise (a blue-black nodule) and an unhealed ulceration.

Name: cutaneous leiomyosarcoma
Definition: A sarcoma and malignant tumor of small intestine that is located_in the small intestine.

Name: cutaneous liposarcoma
Definition: A vulvar sarcoma that has_material_basis in adipocytes.
